						               													<description>SideLinks is a word association game all about conceptually connecting words found on adjacent cards. It can be described simply as a cross between Scrabble and Dominoes but with words.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game contains 140 cards with 560 English words. Each card has four family-friendly words (one per edge) and a point value between 1 and 5. 1-point cards have words with the most connections (some with over 30), while 5-point cards have words with fewer connections. But don't worry, as well over 12,000 connections are known to be available!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are a half a dozen ways to play the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players compete to get the highest score by connecting related words. For example, TEACHER can be connected with STUDENT, SCHOOL, RESPECT, LEARNING, JOB as well as a dozen other words.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Hilarious dialog begins when someone attempts a dubious connection and has to &amp;ldquo;sell&amp;rdquo; it to the group. This makes it a game about connecting people.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Other ways to play include Match, Memory, Grid, Airplane Mode, Secret Connections and Team Secrets.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This family and party game is for use at home and school as well as corporate office team building.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;SideLinks is the next version of the Connections card game, renamed for worldwide distribution as we only had the Canadian trademark for &amp;quot;Connections&amp;quot;. It's a new standalone game with more cards, larger cards, some new rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
